<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3705"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3705-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3705">Natural Desalination - Zero Energy to desalinate and convey to shore&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/7305-4049">Joseph Rizzi</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Natural desalination is the use of natural forces to desalinate sea water. Conveyance from the sea to shore can be done naturally by use of gravity, when horizontal wells are dug from shore to the sea where the desalination takes place. Tidal, Wave, Wind or solar power can bring the water to the surface on shore. Patent pending, no or low royalties. <br/><br/>We are to often looking at other counties in desalination. Water is important to all, and we are running out.<br/><br/>Horizontal drilling is new and under utilized in the water sector. It can be used for sharing water like a web or transporting over long distances and through mountains. <br/><br/>Eco-friendly standard design that is easily expandable. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3705" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3705', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=3705')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3705"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3705"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
